         <abstract>
            <p>In a previous paper it was shown how a probability measure (Eberlein measure) on the closed unit ball of the sequence space, l1, can be used to find the variance σ2 of the error functional for a quadrature formula for the k-dimensional cube, regarded as a random variable. Here we give values of σ for some specific formulae.</p>
         </abstract>
